<a name="5748"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Last call to Enter "Visit Me at CES!" 2012 Exhibitor Video Contest- Deadline Extended to November 4 </div>
<br />


        <img alt="" style="float: right;"  src="/images/content/clapboard2.jpg" />This is the last call to enter the <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/video-contest.htm">2012 Exhibitor Video Contest- Visit Me at CES</a>! You could win a month’s worth of free promotion on the homepage of CESweb.org! You know why CES is one of the most important things your company does each year, and now you can tell everyone else!<br />
        <br />
        Create a short video explaining why your company is exhibiting at 2012 CES and why attendees should visit your booth. Your video much be one minute or less and include your booth number. Help us generate momentum for 2012 CES while creating buzz for your own exhibit!<br />
        <br />
        Five contest winners will be selected based on voting by the general public. The Exhibitor Video Contest voting and winners will be promoted through our attendee newsletter- CES Up to the Minute, CESweb.org and our social media outlets. Get more votes by getting your staff and clients involved as well!<br />
        <br />
        All video entries are due by November 4, 2011. <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/video-contest.htm">Enter today</a>!
    <br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5749"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Get Free Registration for Your Guests Through November</div>
<br />


        <img alt="" style="float: right;"  src="/images/content/NOVBanner_300x250.jpg" />Free registration for the 2012 show ended months ago, but as a CES exhibitor, you have the opportunity to offer your preferred guests and clients free registration up through the end of November 2011. Exhibitor invitations are one of the most cost effective methods of using the branding power of CES to promote your company’s presence at CES.<br />
        <br />
        For this month you can download a series of banner advertisements in different sizes. These banners can be incorporated into your website or electronic messages promoting your presence at CES. These banners will link to a special registration page that gives your guests free registration for November.<br />
        <br />
        With free registration ending one month earlier this year, we know that some of your preferred clients might have missed out on this great opportunity. Be their saviour! Your customers will love getting free advance registration (or reduced-rate on-site registration), and they will love that it came directly from you.<br />
        <br />
        <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/sponsorships/freeOpps.asp#1925">Check out our Exhibitor Invitation page to learn how you can download yours today</a>.
    <br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5747"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Your Company Gets Noticed!</div>
<br />


        <img alt="" style="float: right;"  src="/images/content/FollowMe-PhoneCollage.jpg" />Hundreds of CES attendees are downloading the official CES mobile app, <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/showFloor/followme.asp">Follow Me</a>, every day!<br />
        <br />
        Add your logo for $25, and include product literature for download by users -- before, during and after the tradeshow. Exhibitors who <br />
        include their logo, documents and place ads on the mobile app receive the lion’s share of the hundreds of thousands of mobile app page views!<br />
        <br />
        Far-reaching, cost-effective sponsorships and ad packages are available on the Follow Me mobile app that last for an entire year. Check out our <a  target="_blank" href="http://cesweb.org/docs/2012CES-MobileAdPackages-flyer.pdf">sponsorship and ad package flyer</a> for more information on how to promote your company and your products in this popular medium. Help to build an industry reference tool to where you can direct your potential customers all year long, whenever and wherever they are!
    <br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5750"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">New Designated Passenger Pickup/Drop-off Areas at the LVCC</div>
<br />


        Are you picking up or dropping off a friend or colleague at the LVCC? In order to alleviate vehicular congestion and make it safer to drop off and pick up passengers, we have designated portions of the LVCC Silver 3 Lot and Gold Lot as privately owned vehicle (POV) areas. Passenger vehicles will no longer be allowed curbside access. To pick up or drop off at the South Hall, plan to use the Silver 3 Lot by entering off of Paradise Road. For North and Central Halls, plan to use the Gold Lot at the corner of Paradise and Convention Center Drive by entering off of Convention Center Drive. Note, drivers must remain with their cars; no parking allowed.
    <br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5746"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Go Global for CES</div>
<br />


        <img alt="" style="float: right;"  src="/images/content/doc_logo.JPG" />Are you a U.S. based company looking to grow your international presence? If so, you’ll want to plan to participate in two exciting programs and events organized by the U.S. Department of Commerce. By participating in the Global Market Insight Program, you will have the opportunity to present your products and services to a panel of international industry experts who will provide feedback on finding an appropriate overseas partner, effective international sales strategies, business opportunities in their market and best practices on exporting .There is no cost to participate in the Global Market Insight Program, but registration is required and you must be a CEA member or U.S. exhibitor at the 2012 International CES. <a  target="_blank" href="http://export.gov/industry/infocomm/cesgmip038151.asp">Learn more about this program</a>. <br />
        <br />
        Additionally, the U.S. Department of Commerce is partnering with CEA to host the Global Matchmaking and International Reception at 6 p.m. on Tuesday, January 10. This event connects U.S. consumer electronics companies with hundreds of foreign buyers in a reception setting beyond the show floor - the perfect opportunity for expanding your business into new global markets! Through exhibiting in the Global Matchmaking and International Reception, you can achieve multiple objectives, including export sales, marketing and business development. You'll also meet and prospect new customers, network with foreign buyers and industry professionals and entertain new contacts, partners and clients in a hospitable and professional venue. <a  href="http://export.gov/industry/infocomm/cesgmir038150.asp">Learn more about this event and how to purchase your table-top display</a>.
    <br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5745"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Get More Press Exposure – Exhibit at CES Unveiled@NY</div>
<br />


        <img alt="" style="float: right;"  src="/images/content/CES_Unveiled_event.gif" />What do the following have in common? Reuters, <em>USA Today</em>, <em>The Wall Street Journal</em>, Fox News, BBC, Associated Press, <em>Newsweek</em>, CNN.com, ABC News, Engadget, Gizmodo, and MSNBC.com. If you guessed that they're all media outlets, you're partially right. They were also all in attendance at our 2011 CES Unveiled Events, among more than 1,000 other top media names. <br />
        <br />
        Unveiled@NY on November 8 offers an invaluable opportunity to promote your products in time for the holiday shopping season. Unveiled in Vegas on January 8 gives you the undivided attention of the press two days before CES begins. Already, over 300 media from the northeast have registered for the CES NY Press Preview featuring Unveiled@NY, and we expect more than 1,000 at Unveiled in Las Vegas.<br />
        <br />
        A simple tabletop set-up makes it easy for your team to network with the top industry and consumer media, build relationships, and generate coverage. <br />
        <br />
        Getting the best PR value in the industry, exhibitors receive:
        <ul>
            <li>Exposure to hundreds of influential, credentialed media and analysts. </li>
            <li>Extensive pre-event promotion to CES’ worldwide media list via e-mail, news wires, print materials, direct individual pitching and Web promotion. </li>
            <li>Contact lists of pre-registered and confirmed media/analysts.</li>
            <li>150-word product description and photo in the Unveiled program guide within <em>Consumer Electronics Vision</em> magazine, which is distributed at the press events, to CE Vision’s 25,000 industry readers and to thousands more on-site at the International CES.</li>
            <li>Your product displayed among Innovations 2012 Design and Engineering Awards Honorees’ products – a must-see for press and analysts. </li>
        </ul>
        Sign up today to take advantage of all the pre-event promotional opportunities. <br />
        <br />
        Contact: <a  href="mailto:CESUnveiled@CE.org">CESUnveiled@CE.org</a>. Visit <a  href="http://CESUnveiled@CE.org">CESweb.org/CESUnveiled</a> for more information.
    
